RNA-seq in Bioconductor exercises

Tom Carroll

In todays session we will work with some of the RNA-seq data of adult mouse tissues from Bing Ren’s lab, Liver and Heart. - More information on liver data can be found here - More information on heart data can be found here

  • Precounted RNAseq reads in genes for these tissues can be found as an R data object in /Data/geneCounts_Tissue.RData.

  • Salmon quantification for these tissues can be found in directory /Data/Salmon_Tissue/.

RNA-seq analysis.

  1. Load the /Data/geneCounts_Tissue.RData and create a DESeq2 object. Add 0.25 to every counts and plot a boxplot of the log2 of these updated counts.
## renaming the first element in assays to 'counts'

  1. Run the DEseq workflow function and retrieve normalized counts, add 0.25 to normalised counts and plot a boxplot of the log2 of these updated counts.

  1. Plot the dispersion fit and estimates for our DEseq2 object.

  1. Add a new padj value for all genes. Make a barplot of the number of significantly (padj < 0.05) up and down regulated genes by the original padj values and our new padj values..

  1. Produce an MA-plot before and after logFC shrinkage.
